HEADWORD: Tressured
<hw>Tres"sured</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Her.)</fld>
<def>Provided or bound with a tressure; arranged in the form of a
tressure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>tressured</qex> fleur-de-lis he claims⟦br⟧
To wreathe his shield.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tressy</ent>⟦br⟧
